Release Notes
Default Properties & Backtest Context

The published default strategy properties are chosen to avoid misleading results and to stay within realistic trading conditions:

Initial capital: 25 000 units (retail-friendly account size)

Commission: 0.05 % per trade using strategy.commission.percent

Slippage: 1 tick per order

Risk per trade: 1 % of equity by default, with a maximum of 5 % in the input

Order processing: on bar close

These defaults are used consistently in the script and for the showcased backtests. They are not optimized for any specific market but serve as a reasonable starting point. For meaningful statistics, this strategy should be evaluated on liquid instruments and timeframes that produce well over 100 trades over the tested period (for example, several years of data on 1H or 4H charts of major FX pairs, index futures, or large-cap crypto).

Any performance metrics derived from this strategy (such as profit factor, drawdown, or win rate) will depend strongly on the chosen symbol, timeframe, broker conditions, and parameter settings. They should always be interpreted as instrument- and configuration-specific examples, not as guaranteed or typical results.

